The paper deals with the problem of subspace approximation, which involves finding a low-dimensional linear subspace that best fits a given set of points. This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including computational geometry (cs.CG), data structures (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper uses techniques from convex relaxation and rounding, which are commonly used in optimization and approximation algorithms, and also mentions the Unique Games Conjecture, which is a well-known open problem in theoretical computer science. Based on these factors, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.LG, and cs.NA, in that order.
